s |title=Justin Bieber, Kenny Chesney, Fiona Apple Lead Billboard 200 Debuts |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=June 27, 2012 |accessdate=June 27, 2012}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|3\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Alternative Albums<ref name=\"bb\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Rock Albums<ref name=\"bb\"/>\n|align=\"center\"|1\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Certifications and sales===\n{{certification Table Top}}\n{{certification Table Entry|type=album|title=The Idler Wheel|artist=Fiona Apple|relyear=2012|region=United States|award={{n/a}}|salesamount=205,000|certref=<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/articles/news/1568686/christopher-tricky-stewart-exits-epic-ar-helm|title=Christopher 'Tricky' Stewart Exits Epic A&R Helm\n|publisher=Billboard |date=June 28, 2013 |accessdate=April 20, 2018}}</ref>}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2012)\n!scope=\"col\"|Position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US ''Billboard'' 200<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2012/the-billboard-200?begin=141&order=position |title=Billboard 200 Albums \u2013 2012 Year End Charts |work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |accessdate=December 16, 2012}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|157\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Alternative Albums<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2012/top-alternative-albums?begin=21&order=position |title=Alternative Albums \u2013 2012 Year End Charts |work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |accessdate=December 16, 2012}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|28\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|US Rock Albums<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/year-end/2012/top-rock-albums?begin=41&order=position |title=Rock Albums \u2013 2012 Year End Charts |work=Billboard |publisher=Prometheus Global Media |accessdate=December 16, 2012}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|48\n|}\n{{col-end}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{notelist}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Fiona Apple}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Idler Wheel}}\n[[Category:2012 albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Charley Drayton]]\n[[Category:Epic Records albums]]\n[[Category:Fiona Apple albums]]\n[[Category:Folk albums by American artists]]\n[[Category:Folktronica albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{about|the Fiona Apple album|the wheel|Idler-wheel}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = The Idler Wheel...\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Fiona Apple]]\n| cover      = TheIdlerWheel....jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|2012|6|18}}\n| recorded   = 2008\u20132011\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n* Stanley ([[Los Feliz, California]])\n* NBB (New York City)\n| genre      = [[Art pop]]<ref>https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-album-reviews/the-idler-wheel-204355/</ref>\n| length     = 42:39\n| label      =\n* Clean Slate\n* [[Epic Records|Epic]]\n| producer   =\n* Fiona Apple\n* [[Charley Drayton]]{{efn|Credited as \"Feedy\" and \"Seedy\" respectively}}\n| prev_title = [[iTunes Originals \u2013 Fiona Apple]]\n| prev_year  = 2006\n| next_title = [[Fetch the Bolt Cutters]]\n| next_year  = 2020\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = The Idler Wheel...\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = [[Every Single Night]]\n | single1date = May 8, 2012\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do''''', frequently abridged as '''''The Idler Wheel...''''', is the fourth and most recent studio album by [[Fiona Apple]]. Like her second album ''[[When the Pawn...]]'', its title derives from a poem written by Apple herself.<ref>{{cite web |last=Perpetua |first=Matthew |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/fiona-apple-unveils-23-word-album-title-20120307 |title=Fiona Apple Unveils 23-Word Album Title |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |publisher=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]] |date=March 7, 2012 |accessdate=March 7, 2012}}</ref> It was released in the UK on June 18, 2012<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.popmatters.com/159931-fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-2495841224.html |title=Fiona Apple: The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw... |work=PopMatters |date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=January 26, 2019 |author=Chiola, Enio}}</ref> and in the US on June 19 by [[Epic Records]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Battan |first=Carrie |url=https://www.pitchfork.com/news/45671-fiona-apple-reveals-album-title/ |title=Fiona Apple Reveals Album Title |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=March 7, 2012 |accessdate=March 7, 2012}}</ref> The album debuted at number three on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], her highest debut yet, selling 72,000 copies in its first week.<ref name=\"bbdebut\"/> The album received a nomination at the [[2013 Grammy Awards]] for [[Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album|Best Alternative Album]].<ref name=\"grammy.com\">{{cite news|url=http://www.grammy.com/nominees |title=The 55th Grammy Awards Nominees List |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5ugg4pB5Y |archivedate=2010-12-03 }}</ref> The album was included in best of the year lists by several publications.\n\n==Background and release==\nFollowing the delays and controversy surrounding the release of ''[[Extraordinary Machine]]'' (2005), Apple began recording new material for her fourth studio album in secret, including from her label, [[Epic Records]]. When asked by ''[[BlackBook (magazine)|BlackBook]]'' magazine when the recording sessions began, Apple remarked, \"It must have started in 2008. Or 2009. I don't know! I have no idea. It's weird to think that there was 2008, 2009, 2010, 2011. Where've I been? What was I doing? What was that year about?\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Coates |first=Tyler |url=http://www.blackbookmag.com/music/the-long-and-winding-road-that-leads-to-fiona-apple-1.49114 |title=The Long and Winding Road That Leads to Fiona Apple |work=[[BlackBook (magazine)|BlackBook]] |publisher=Vibe Media |date=May 31, 2012 |accessdate=June 3, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120603033544/http://www.blackbookmag.com/music/the-long-and-winding-road-that-leads-to-fiona-apple-1.49114 |archivedate=June 3, 2012 }}</ref> Apple elaborated,\n{{cquote|It was very casual, and I wasn't fully admitting that I was making an album, I got to use the time in the studio to inspire me to finish other things rather than feel like I was finishing homework to hand in. It wasn't a lot of pressure. And the record company didn't know I was doing it, so nobody was looking over my shoulder.}} Instead of her long-time collaborator [[Jon Brion]], Apple opted to produce the album with her touring drummer, [[Charley Drayton]].<ref name=\"NYTimes\">{{cite news |last=Pareles |first=Jon |authorlink=Jon Pareles |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/06/03/arts/music/fiona-apples-new-album-the-idler-wheel.html?_r=1&pagewanted=all |title=Fiona Apple Faces Outward |work=[[The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The New York Times Company]] |date=May 30, 2012 |accessdate=June 3, 2012}}</ref> Executives at Epic found out that Apple had recorded an album in early 2012, when she presented it to them.<ref>{{cite web |last=Baron |first=Zach |url=https://www.spin.com/2012/05/fiona-apples-return-idle-no-more/?page=3 |title=Fiona Apple's Return: Idle No More |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |date=May 31, 2012 |accessdate=June 3, 2012}}</ref> The album was originally planned for release in 2011, but Apple delayed the release until her label found a new president in 2012, explaining that she \"didn't want her work to be mishandled amid corporate disarray.\"<ref name=\"NYTimes\"/> During a secret concert in Los Angeles with Brion, Apple remarked, \"I can't remember any of my new songs because they've been done for a fucking year.\"<ref>{{cite web |last=Baltin |first=Steve |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/fiona-apple-previews-new-material-at-sxsw-show-20120315 |title=Fiona Apple Previews New Material At SXSW Show |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |publisher=[[Jann Wenner|Wenner Media]] |date=March 15, 2012 |accessdate=June 3, 2012}}</ref> In January 2012, [[L.A. Reid]] announced through [[Twitter]] that new material from Apple would be released later in 2012.<ref>{{cite web |last=Mitchell |first=Jon |url=http://newsroom.mtv.com/2012/01/24/la-reid-confirms-new-fiona-apple-music-is-on-the-way/ |title=LA Reid Confirms New Fiona Apple Music Is On The Way |publisher=[[MTV News]]. [[MTV Networks]] |date=January 24, 2012 |accessdate=June 3, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Bain |first=Becky |url=http://idolator.com/6151291/fiona-apple-new-album-la-reid |title=L.A. Reid Confirms New Fiona Apple Music On The Way |publisher=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]. [[Buzz Media]] |date=January 24, 2012 |accessdate=June 3, 2012|quote=Lot's {{sic}} of good music coming from Epic_Records in the next few weeks. Stay tuned music fans. Welcome back Fiona!}}</ref>\n\n==Promotion==\nApple announced [[The Idler Wheel Tour|a small tour]] in Spring 2012 prompting speculation over a new album.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/02/21/fiona-apple-tour-dates-2012-sxsw/|title=Fiona Apple will play at least eight live shows this year -- find the details here|first=Ray|last=Rahman|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=March 20, 2012|date=February 21, 2012}}</ref> Ahead of her first performance on the tour, the album and its title were announced.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/45671-fiona-apple-reveals-album-title|title=Fiona Apple Reveals Album Title|first=Carrie|last=Battan|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|accessdate=March 7, 2012|date=February 21, 2012}}</ref> The tour marked Apple's first performances outside of [[Los Angeles]] in over five years.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/03/15/fiona-apple-sxsw-video-npr-showcase_n_1346947.html|title=Fiona Apple SXSW: Singer Performs Seven Years After Her Last Album (VIDEO, PHOTOS)|first=Chris|last=Talbott|work=[[Huffington Post]]|accessdate=March 20, 2012|date=March 15, 2012}}</ref> Apple kicked off the tour with two performances at the [[South by Southwest Festival]] where she debuted three new songs from ''The Idler Wheel...''.The album's first single, \"[[Every Single Night]]\", received positive reviews and was well received by fans and critics. ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'}}s Jenn Pelly gave the song their Best New Music designation the same day.<ref>\n{{cite web|url=https://www.popmatters.com/pm/post/155991-sxsw-music-day-2-fiona-apple-at-pitchfork-showcase/|title=SXSW Music Day 3: Fiona Apple + Grimes (Pitchfork Showcase)|first=|last=|work=[[Pop Matters]]|accessdate=March 20, 2012|date=March 15, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/03/19/fiona-apple-valentine_n_1362819.html|title=Fiona Apple's Valentine: Artist Performs New Song Live At SXSW (VIDEO)|first=Amber|last=Genuske|work=[[Huffington Post]]|accessdate=March 20, 2012|date=March 19, 2012}}</ref> She released a video for the track \"Hot Knife\" on July 24, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/51611-watch-fiona-apples-hot-knife-video-directed-by-paul-thomas-anderson/|title=Watch Fiona Apple's \"Hot Knife\" Video, Directed by Paul Thomas Anderson|last=Battan|first=Carrie|date=July 24, 2013|access-date=April 28, 2018}}\n</ref>\n\nOn June 19, 2012, the same day that ''The Idler Wheel...'' was released, Apple began [[The Idler Wheel Tour|an expansive North American tour]] to promote the album. The tour kicked off in Ithaca, New York, and finished on July 29 at the Hollywood Palladium. On June 24, Apple performed at the Sunday portion of New York City's Governors Ball Music Festival, which featured acts such as  [[Modest Mouse]], [[Explosions in the Sky]] and [[Beck]], among others.<ref name= \"MTV\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1682708/fiona-apple-tour-dates.jhtml|title=Fiona Apple Announces North American Tour Dates|first=James|last=Montgomery|publisher=[[MTV]]|accessdate=March 20, 2012|date=March 19, 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe music video for \"[[Every Single Night]]\" premiered on the [[Sundance Channel (United States)|Sundance Channel]] on June 10<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sundancechannel.com/sunfiltered/2012/06/fiona-apple-premiere/|title=Watch: Exclusive premiere of Fiona Apple's new video EVERY SINGLE NIGHT|first=|last=|publisher=[[Sundance Channel (United States)|Sundance Channel]]|accessdate=June 10, 2012|date=June 10, 2012}}</ref> and was directed by Joseph Cahill.<ref>{{cite news|title=Video: Fiona Apple: \"Every Single Night\"|url=https://pitchfork.com/news/46795-video-fiona-apple-every-single-night/|accessdate=June 11, 2012|date=June 9, 2012}}</ref> On the same day the entire album streamed online on [[NPR]].<ref name=\"NPR\">[https://www.npr.org/2012/06/10/154422085/first-listen-fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel First Listen: Fiona Apple, 'The Idler Wheel...'] NPR Music. June 10, 2012</ref> On June 18, Apple made her first television appearance since 2006 on ''[[Late Night with Jimmy Fallon]]''. Apple performed \"Anything We Want\" with [[The Roots]] and celebrated [[Paul McCartney]]'s 70th birthday by performing \"[[Let Me Roll It]]\" with Jimmy Fallon performing back-up vocals.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://stereogum.com/1068841/watch-fiona-apple-play-fallon/video/|title=Watch Fiona Apple Play Fallon|first=Tom|last=Breihan|publisher=[[Stereogum]]|accessdate=June 21, 2012|date=June 19, 2012}}</ref>\n\n==Critical reception==\n{{Album ratings\n| ADM = 8.5/10<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.anydecentmusic.com/review/4646/Fiona-Apple-The-Idler-Wheel-Is-Wiser-Than-The-Driver-Of-The-Screw-And-Whipping-Cords-Will-Serve-You-More-Than-Ropes-Will-Ever-Do.aspx |title=The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than The Driver Of The Screw And Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do by Fiona Apple reviews |publisher=[[AnyDecentMusic?]] |accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref>\n| MC = 89/100<ref name=\"MC\">{{cite web |url=http://www.metacritic.com/music/the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driver-of-the-screw-and-whipping-cords-will-serve-you-more-than-ro |title=Reviews for The Idler Wheel Is Wiser than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More than Ropes Will Ever Do by Fiona Apple |publisher=[[Metacritic]] |accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]] \n| rev1Score = {{Rating|5|5}}<ref name=\"allmusic\">{{cite web |last=Erlewine |first=Stephen Thomas |authorlink=Stephen Thomas Erlewine |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driver-of-the-screw-and-whipping-cords-will-serve-you-more-than-ropes-will-ever-do-mw0002332951|title=The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do \u2013 Fiona Apple |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=November 16, 2019}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[The A.V. Club]]''\n| rev2score = A<ref name=\"AV\">{{cite web |last=Koski |first=Genevieve |url=https://www.avclub.com/articles/fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driv,81286/ |title=Fiona Apple: The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than The Driver Of The Screw And Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do |work=[[The A.V. Club]] |date=June 19, 2012 |accessdate=January 26, 2016}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]''\n| rev3Score = A<ref name=\"EW\">{{cite journal |last=Maerz |first=Melissa |url=https://www.ew.com/ew/article/0,,20603579,00.html |title=The Idler Wheel... review \u2013 Fiona Apple |work=[[Entertainment Weekly]] |date=June 14, 2012 |accessdate=June 14, 2012}}</ref>\n| rev4 = ''[[The Guardian]]''\n| rev4Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite news |last=Simpson |first=Dave |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/dec/20/fiona-apple-idler-wheel-review |title=Fiona Apple: The Idler Wheel \u2026 \u2013 review |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=December 20, 2012 |accessdate=December 20, 2012}}</ref>\n| rev5 = ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''\n| rev5Score = {{Rating|4|4}}<ref name=\"Los Angeles Times\">{{cite news |last=Roberts |first=Randall |url=http://latimesblogs.latimes.com/music_blog/2012/06/album-review-fiona-apples-the-idler-wheel-.html |title=Album review: Fiona Apple's 'The Idler Wheel ...' |work=[[Los Angeles Times]] |date=June 19, 2012 |accessdate=June 19, 2012}}</ref>\n| rev6 = ''[[MSN Music]]'' ([[Robert Christgau#Consumer Guide|Expert Witness]])\n| rev6Score = A\u2212<ref name=\"Christgau\">{{cite web |last=Christgau |first=Robert |authorlink=Robert Christgau |date=July 24, 2012 |url=http://www.robertchristgau.com/xg/cg/ew2012-07.php |title=Fiona Apple/Regina Spektor |work=[[MSN Music]] |accessdate=July 24, 2012}}</ref>\n| rev7 = ''[[NME]]''\n| rev7Score = 8/10<ref name=\"nme\">{{cite web |last=Elan |first=Priya |url=https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/reviews-fiona-apple-13311 |title=Fiona Apple \u2013 'The Idler Wheel...' |work=[[NME]] |date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=June 18, 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141109025639/http://www.nme.com/reviews/fiona-apple/13311 |archivedate=November 9, 2014}}</ref>\n| rev8 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev8Score = 9.0/10<ref name=\"Pitchfork\">{{cite web |last=Dombal |first=Ryan |url=https://www.pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/16732-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driver-of-the-screw-and-whipping-cords-will-serve-you-more-than-ropes-will-ever-do/ |title=Fiona Apple: The Idler Wheel... |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>\n| rev9 = ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\n| rev9Score = {{Rating|3.5|5}}<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\">{{cite web |last=Rosen |first=Jody |authorlink=Jody Rosen |url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/albumreviews/the-idler-wheel-20120619 |title=The Idler Wheel... |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=June 19, 2012 |accessdate=June 20, 2012}}</ref>\n| rev10 = ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]''\n| rev10Score = 8/10<ref name=\"Spin\">{{cite web |last=Hopper |first=Jessica |url=https://www.spin.com/2012/06/fiona-apple-idler-wheel-wiser-driver-screw-and-whipping-cords-will-serve-you-more-ropes-will/|title=Fiona Apple, 'The Idler Wheel is wiser than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords will serve you more than Ropes will ever do' (Epic) |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>\n}}\n''The Idler Wheel...'' was praised by music critics. At [[Metacritic]], which assigns a [[standard score|normalized]] rating out of 100 to reviews from mainstream critics, the album received an [[weighted mean|average]] score of 89, based on 35 reviews, which indicates \"universal acclaim\".<ref name=\"MC\"/> \n[[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] of [[AllMusic]] awarded the album it five stars out of five, praising Apple's \"magnetic vocals, the human element pulling us into these songs\", adding that while the album has similarities to her previous three, it is \"stripped of all her carnivalesque accouterments\" and there is a new \"unwavering determination and cohesion\".<ref name=\"allmusic\"/> [[BBC Music]] reviewer James Skinner praised the \"hopelessly romantic\" album and her \"expressive\" vocals, and considered the album to be her \"sparsest work to date\".<ref>{{cite web |last=Skinner |first=James |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/reviews/j2d3 |title=Review of Fiona Apple \u2013 The Idler Wheel... |publisher=[[BBC Music]]|date=June 11, 2012 |accessdate=June 11, 2012}}</ref> Blair Kelly of ''[[musicOMH]]'' said the blame is \"both roaring with rage and swooning with romance\", finding it refreshingly \"spare\" while its focus is on Apple's \"raw, rough and flawed\" vocals.\"<ref name=\"omh\">{{cite web |first=Blair |last=Kelly |url=http://www.musicomh.com/albums/fiona-apple-2_0612.htm |title=Fiona Apple \u2013 The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than The Driver Of The Screw And Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do |work=[[musicOMH]] |accessdate=June 12, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120616121437/http://www.musicomh.com/albums/fiona-apple-2_0612.htm|archivedate=June 16, 2012}}</ref> ''[[American Songwriter]]'' writer Jim Beviglia rated the album four-stars-out-of-five, praising its \"stark and raw\" songs, its \"visceral power\" and Apple's presentation of \"the mixed emotions that accompany the fallout of a broken relationship\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.americansongwriter.com/2012/06/fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel/|title=Fiona Apple - The Idler Wheel... Review |work=[[American Songwriter]]|first=Jim|last=Beviglia|date=June 13, 2012|accessdate=June 13, 2012}}</ref>\n\n[[Robert Christgau]] gave the album an A\u2212, calling it \"damn catchy\", with \"few arpeggios, and not much tone color and such\", and while Apple \"executes simple figures and hammers thick chords, including a few boogie-woogies just to make a point\", the album is \"mood music\".<ref name=\"Christgau\"/> Melissa Maerz of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the album an A, and regarded it as \"highly confessional and creative and temperamental\", concluding it \"isn't easy listening. But it's worth it.\"<ref name=\"EW\"/> Ryan Dombal of ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'' scored the album nine out of ten and called it \"the most distilled Fiona Apple album yet, commending its \"raw emotion\".<ref name=\"Pitchfork\"/> ''[[Consequence of Sound]]'' called the album \"one of the most daring pop records in recent history\", awarding it with four-and-a-half stars out of five.\"<ref name=\"Larson\">{{cite web |last=Larson |first=Jeremy D. |url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/06/album-review-fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel/ |title=Album Review: Fiona Apple \u2013 ''The Idler Wheel\u2026'' |work=[[Consequence of Sound]] |date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=June 19, 2012}}</ref> Greg Kot of ''[[Chicago Tribune]]'' gave it three-and-a-half stars out of four, deeming it \"more stripped down and turbulent than before\", adding that \"It makes for a raw, unsettling listen, tempered by shots of dark humor.\"<ref name=\"CT\">{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/turnitup/chi-fiona-apple-album-review-the-idler-wheel-reviewed-20120618,0,5611603.column|title=Album review: Fiona Apple, 'The Idler Wheel ...'|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|first=Greg|last=Kot|date=2012-06-18|accessdate=2012-06-18}}</ref> ''[[NME]]'' wrote: \"The tension created by the lyrics and music is wonderful and uneasy, ensuring that ''The Idler Wheel...'' is endlessly fascinating and unlike anything else you're likely to hear this year.\"<ref name=\"nme\"/>\n\nJessica Hopper of ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'' rated the album eight out of ten, writing that it \"relentlessly reassures us that she\u2019s the same old Fiona, still wilding and Weill-ing out\" and \"the unexpected triumph lies not in the spectacle of the singer raw-dogging her emotions, but in her total command of the anarchy that results\".<ref name=\"Spin\"/> ''[[Slant Magazine]]'' gave it four-stars-out-of-five and called the album \"her most dense and ambitious\" while it remains \"accessible\".<ref name=\"Slant\">{{cite web |last=Keefe |first=Jonathan |url=https://www.slantmagazine.com/music/review/fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driver-of-the-screw-and-whipping-cords-will-serve-you-more-than-ropes-will-ever-do/2803 |title=Fiona Apple: The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw, and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do |work=[[Slant Magazine]]|date=June 18, 2012 |accessdate=June 18, 2012}}</ref>'' Genevieve Ksoki of [[The A.V. Club]]'' graded the album an A and said: \"The beauty of ''The Idler Wheel...'' is how it transmits each of those feelings in excruciating, frank, and lovely detail.\"<ref name=\"AV\"/> Jillian Mapes of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' wrote that although the album is \"devoid of much musical flourishing\", it was \"absolutely worth the seven-year wait\".<ref name=\"Billboard\">{{cite web |last=Mapes |first=Jillian |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/review/1066945/fiona-apples-the-idler-wheel-track-by-track-review |title=Fiona Apple's \"The Idler Wheel...\": Track-by-Track Review |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |date=2012-06-19 |accessdate=2012-06-19}}</ref> ''[[The Boston Phoenix]]''{{'}}s Zeth Lundy rated the album three-and-a-half stars out of four, describing its sound as \"raw and deceptively artless\" and deeming it \"arguably her funniest ... but also her leanest and most melodically daring.\"<ref name=\"The Boston Phoenix\">{{cite web|url=http://thephoenix.com/Boston/music/140302-fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-dr/|title=Fiona Apple's The Idler Wheel is wiser than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords will serve you more than Ropes will ever do - review|work=[[The Boston Phoenix]]|first=Zeth|last=Lundy|date=2012-06-19|accessdate=2012-06-19|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130217124859/http://thephoenix.com/Boston/music/140302-fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-dr/|archivedate=February 17, 2013}}</ref> ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'' magazine reviewer Stephen M. Deusner rated it 8.4 out of 10, stating that Applies relies on the same eccentricities of her past work, and her inability to \"get out of her own head \u2014 can\u2019t even begin to write a song that doesn\u2019t build on layers of self-conscious self-absorption and gritty self-loathing \u2014 may in fact be one of her greatest and most distinguishing strengths as an artist\"; while her \"overwrought\" lyrics \"can provoke cringes as easily as sympathetic nods\", they \"exert a considerable power, marking these songs as indelibly her own\".<ref name=\"Paste\">{{cite web|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2012/06/fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driv.html|title=Fiona Apple: The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do REVIEW|work=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|first=Stephen M.|last=Deusner|date=2012-06-19|accessdate=2012-06-19}}</ref> ''[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]'' magazine gave the album four out of five stars, writing: \"Apple's return to music is not only undeniably powerful, but ''Idler'' is arguably her best work yet.\"<ref name=\"now\">{{cite web|url=https://nowtoronto.com/music/album-reviews/fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driver-of-the-screw-and-whipping-cords-will-serve-you-more-than-ropes-will-ever-do/|title=Fiona Apple - The Idler Wheel... REVIEW|work=[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]|first=Benjamin|last=Boles|date=2012-06-19|accessdate=2012-06-19}}</ref>\n\n''[[PopMatters]]''{{'}} Enio Chiola rated the album six out of ten, finding it \"purposefully and inauthentically difficult for the sake of being difficult\", criticizing the \"twist[ing] [of] simple arrangements and sentiments into an unnecessarily uneasy listen...[resulting] in the record being often times tiresome and boring\" and Apple's \"tendency to scream\". \"There simply isn\u2019t enough variation\" on the album, Chiola concluded, but it \"isn't necessarily (even at its core) a bad record.\"<ref name=\"PopMatters\">{{cite web |last=Chiola |first=Enio |url=https://www.popmatters.com/159931-fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-2495841224.html |title=Fiona Apple: The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw... |work=[[PopMatters]]  |date=June 19, 2012 |accessdate=June 19, 2012}}</ref> ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' gave the album three-and-a-half out of five stars, writing that the album is \"rawboned emotionally\" while Apple \"pours out her distress on driving songs with lyrics that mix romantic poetry and therapy-speak \u2013 Byron by way of Oprah\", and although the songs may \"drag\", her \"kooky energy pushes through the slow spots.\"<ref name=\"Rolling Stone\"/>\n\n===Awards and year-end lists===\nThe album received a nomination at the [[55th Grammy Awards]] for [[Grammy Award for Best Alternative Music Album|Best Alternative Album]].<ref name=\"grammy.com\"/> It was named the best album of 2012 by ''[[Time Magazine]]'', ''[[Stereogum]]'', ''[[Spinner (website)|Spinner]]'', and [[NPR Music]]'s ''[[Fresh Air]]''.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://entertainment.time.com/2012/12/04/top-10-albums/slide/all/|title=Top 10 Albums|work=[[Time Magazine]]|date=December 5, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://stereogum.com/1210661/stereogums-top-50-albums-of-2012/franchises/listomania/|title=Stereogum's Top 50 Albums Of 2012|work=[[Stereogum]]|date=December 5, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.spinner.com/2012/12/07/50-best-albums-of-2012-list/|title=50 Best Albums of 2012 List|work=[[Spinner (website)|Spinner]]|date=December 7, 2012|accessdate=December 15, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130109175601/http://www.spinner.com/2012/12/07/50-best-albums-of-2012-list/|archivedate=January 9, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.npr.org/sections/bestmusic2012/2012/12/18/167278615/ken-tuckers-top-10-albums-of-2012|title=Ken Tucker's Top 10 Albums Of 2012|first=Ken|last=Tucker|work=[[Fresh Air]]|date=December 18, 2012|accessdate=December 18, 2012}}</ref> It ranked at number 2 on the lists of ''[[Consequence of Sound]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/12/albums-of-the-year-2012/|title=Top 50 Albums 2012|work=[[Consequence of Sound]]|date=December 14, 2012|accessdate=December 15, 2012}}</ref> and ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ew.com/gallery/10-best-albums-2012/#2-fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-is-wiser-than-the-driver-of-the-screw-and-whipping-cords-will-serve-you-more-than-ropes-will-ever-do|title=10 Best Albums of 2012|last=Maerz|first=Melissa|date=December 11, 2012|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=December 18, 2012}}</ref> number 3 on the lists of ''[[USA Today]]'' and ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/popcandy/2012/11/21/top-albums-of-2012/1719319/|title=The top albums of 2012|first=Sean|last=McCarthy|work=[[USA Today]]|date=November 21, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://pitchfork.com/features/staff-lists/9017-the-top-50-albums-of-2012/5/ |title=Staff Lists: The Top 50 Albums of 2012 |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |date=December 20, 2012 |accessdate=December 22, 2012}}</ref> number 4 on ''[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/blogs/lists/2012/11/the-50-best-albums-of-2012.html|title=The 50 Best Albums of 2012|work=[[Paste (magazine)|Paste]]|date=November 26, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012|last=Jackson|first=Josh}}</ref> number 5 in ''[[Rolling Stone]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://stereogum.com/1213142/rolling-stones-50-best-albums-of-2012/list/|title=Rolling Stone's 50 Best Albums Of 2012|first=Michael|last=Nelson|work=[[Stereogum]]|date=December 5, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> number 10 on [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://idolator.com/photos/best-albums-2012-year/fiona-apple-the-idler-wheel-2|title=2012\u2032s Best Music|first=Robbie|last=Daw|work=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|date=December 5, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref>  number sixteen in ''[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.spin.com/2012/12/best-albums-2012/121130-16-fiona/|title=SPIN's 50 Best Albums of 2012|first=|last=|work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]]|date=December 3, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> number seventeen on ''[[American Songwriter]]''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.americansongwriter.com/2012/12/american-songwriters-top-50-albums-of-2012/4/|title=Top 50 Albums of 2012|first=|last=|work=[[American Songwriter]]|date=December 4, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> and ''[[Filter (magazine)|Filter]]'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://filtermagazine.com/index.php/news/entry/filters_top_10_of_2012_staff_picks|title=FILTER's Top 10 of 2012: Staff Picks|work=[[Filter (magazine)|Filter]]|date=December 3, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> and appeared on [[NPR]]'s unnumbered list.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://stereogum.com/1213131/nprs-50-favorite-albums-of-2012/list/|title=NPR's 50 Favorite Albums Of 2012|first=Tom|last=Breihan|work=[[Stereogum]]|date=December 5, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> The album was ranked #10 in ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'s}} list of The 100 Best Albums of the Decade So Far (2010-2014), published in August 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/staff-lists/9465-the-top-100-albums-of-2010-2014/5/ |title=The Top 100 Albums of 2010-2014 |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]}}</ref>\n\nApple's track \"Hot Knife\" ranked at number twelve in ''[[Rolling Stone]]''\u2019s 50 Best Songs of 2012 list<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/lists/50-best-songs-of-2012-20121205/fiona-apple-hot-knife-19691231|title=50 BEST SONGS OF 2012|first=|last=|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=December 5, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> and \"[[Every Single Night]]\" ranked at number 7 on ''[[American Songwriter]]''s Top 50 Songs of 2012.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.americansongwriter.com/2012/12/american-songwriters-top-50-songs-of-2012/2/|title=Top 50 Songs of 2012|first=|last=|work=[[American Songwriter]]|date=December 4, 2012|accessdate=December 6, 2012}}</ref> In ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'}}s Top 100 Tracks of 2012, \"Werewolf\" was ranked at number 9 and \"Every Single Night\" was ranked at number 35.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://pitchfork.com/features/staff-lists/9015-the-top-100-tracks-of-2012/11/|title=The Top 100 Tracks of 2012|first=|last=|work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]|date=December 17, 2012|accessdate=December 29, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, the album was included on ''[[The Guardian]]'''s 100 Best Albums of the 21st Century list,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2019/sep/13/100-best-albums-of-the-21st-century |title=The 100 best albums of the 21st century |work=The Gaurdian |date=13 September 2019 |accessdate=18 September 2019 }}</ref> and ranked 5th on ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''{{'s}} list of The 200 Best Albums of the 2010s.<ref>{{cite web |title=The 200 Best Albums of the 2010s |url=https://pitchfork.com/features/lists-and-guides/the-200-best-albums-of-the-2010s/ |website=Pitchfork |accessdate=9 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| all_writing     = Fiona Apple\n| total_length    = 42:39\n| title1          = [[Every Single Night]]\n| length1         = 3:29\n| title2          = Daredevil\n| length2         = 3:28\n| title3          = Valentine\n| length3         = 3:32\n| title4          = Jonathan\n| length4         = 5:03\n| title5          = Left Alone\n| length5         = 4:50\n| title6          = Werewolf\n| length6         = 3:12\n| title7          = Periphery\n| length7         = 4:58\n| title8          = Regret\n| length8         = 5:17\n| title9          = Anything We Want\n| length9         = 4:40\n| title10         = Hot Knife\n| length10        = 4:02\n}}\n{{Tracklist\n| headline        = [[iTunes Store|iTunes]] deluxe edition bonus track<ref>{{cite web |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/idler-wheel-is-wiser-than/id531456290 |title=The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do (Deluxe Version) by Fiona Apple |publisher=[[iTunes Store]] US. [[Apple Inc.|Apple Inc]] |accessdate=August 18, 2012}}</ref>\n| title11         = Largo\n| length11        = 2:41\n| total_length    = 45:20\n}}\n{{Track listing\n| headline        = Deluxe edition bonus DVD \u2013\u00a0filmed at [[South by Southwest|SXSW]], March 14, 2012\n| title1          = Every Single Night\n| note1           = live\n| length1         = 3:19\n| title2          = Anything We Want\n| note2           = live\n| length2         = 5:00\n| title3          = [[Fast as You Can]]\n| note3           = live\n| length3         = 5:15\n| title4          = [[A Mistake]]\n| note4           = live\n| length4         = 5:53\n| title5          = [[Sleep to Dream]]\n| note5           = live\n| length5         = 4:40\n| total_length    = 24:07\n}}\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from ''The Idler Wheel...'' album liner notes.<ref>{{cite AV media notes |title=The Idler Wheel Is Wiser Than the Driver of the Screw and Whipping Cords Will Serve You More Than Ropes Will Ever Do |others=[[Fiona Apple]] |year=2012 |type=CD liner notes |publisher=[[Epic Records]] |id=88691978632}}</ref>\n\n* [[Fiona Apple]] (credited as \"Feedy\") \u2013 field recording, loops, truck stomping, dance partner, thighs on \"Daredevil\", percussion, piano,[[celesta|celeste]], [[timpani]] on \"Hot Knife\", voice strings, singing, artwork, bass keyboard, production\n* [[Charley Drayton]] (credited as \"Seedy\") \u2013 [[kora (instrument)|kora]], [[autoharp]], truck stomping, dance partner, percussion, guitar, [[bouzouki]], marimba, drum set, voice strings, thighs on \"Daredevil\", field recording, pillow, voice of pain, baritone vocals, string harp, [[Teisco]] guitar, production \n* [[John Would]] \u2013 recording\n* Eddison Sainsbury \u2013 recording\n* [[Dave Way]] \u2013 mixing\n* [[Howie Weinberg]] \u2013 mastering\n* Dan Gerbarg \u2013 mastering\n* [[Sebastian Steinberg]] \u2013 acoustic bass, [[Harmony Company|Harmony]] guitar\n* [[Maude Maggart]] \u2013 high harmony on \"Hot Knife\"\n* Eric Roinestad \u2013 art direction, design\n* Andrew Slater \u2013 management\n\n==Charts==\n{{col-begin}}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Weekly charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|-\n!scope=\"col\"|Chart (2012)\n!scope=\"col\"|Peak<br>position\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[ARIA Charts|Australian Albums Chart]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Fiona+Apple&titel=The+Idler+Wheel+Is+Wiser+Than+The+Driver+Of+The+Screw+And+Whipping+Cords+Will+Serve+You+More+Than+Ropes+